{"builtWith":"0.15.15","comments":[{"LineComment":" ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━"},{"LineComment":"                                     // hydrogen // schema // canvas"},{"LineComment":" ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━"},{"LineComment":" | Canvas — The 2D void where everything exists."},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | ## Design Philosophy"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | The canvas is the universal substrate. It provides:"},{"LineComment":" | - **Bounds**: Finite region where content exists"},{"LineComment":" | - **Physics**: Device orientation mapped to world gravity"},{"LineComment":" | - **Grid**: Cell subdivision for simulation"},{"LineComment":" | - **Background**: What the void looks like"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | ## Architectural Position"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | Canvas is WHERE things exist. It defines the coordinate system and"},{"LineComment":" | physics context. Surface defines WHAT things look like. Physics"},{"LineComment":" | defines HOW things move. Spatial defines 3D structure."},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | ## Paint Flow Model"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | When device tilts:"},{"LineComment":" | 1. Canvas/Physics converts orientation to gravity vector"},{"LineComment":" | 2. Gravity direction is projected onto 2D canvas plane"},{"LineComment":" | 3. Physics/Fluid runs simulation on Canvas/Grid cells"},{"LineComment":" | 4. Surface/Height tracks paint pile depth"},{"LineComment":" | 5. When height exceeds viscosity threshold, flow/topple triggers"},{"LineComment":" |"},{"LineComment":" | ## Dependencies"},{"LineComment":" | - Hydrogen.Schema.Canvas.Bounds"},{"LineComment":" | - Hydrogen.Schema.Canvas.Physics"},{"LineComment":" | - Hydrogen.Schema.Canvas.Grid"},{"LineComment":" | - Hydrogen.Schema.Canvas.Background"}],"decls":[],"exports":[],"foreign":[],"imports":[{"annotation":{"meta"